LTORG(Literal Origin) - assign addresses to literals
END - assembler code ka ending / assigns addresses to literals.
Assembler directives main location counter nhi likhte hain
within same pooltab, if literals repeat- then dont add it in table
if literals are there in different pooltab, then it should be written in table
whenever any symbol comes in s1 position, then its location counter is the address
if the symbol comes at any other position than s1, then it only gets stored in symbol table.
